Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.28,1:18:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,whatchamacallit that we gave the people\Nand that worked extremely well. Sort of
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.04,1:18:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,wandering around kind of a thing. Can we\Ndo that, Robert?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.23,1:18:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yep.\N>> Yeah. Can we do it today?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.67,1:19:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,>> We're not ready for it, but we'll try.\N>> Yeah. It's just a different experiment.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.60,1:19:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So, spiritual work, it has to\Ndo with purification.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.08,1:19:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, "How come I feel worse since\NI got involved in spiritual work?"
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.32,1:19:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because the overall context now is\Ndifferent. Uh the overall context is to
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.19,1:19:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,transcend limitation.\NSo once you commit to reaching the state
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.80,1:19:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of enlightenment or advanced levels of\Nconsciousness or unconditional love
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.32,1:19:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever works\Nyou started the process of purification
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.40,1:19:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and the process of purification brings\Nup all which needs to be purified
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.40,1:19:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,right\Nthe dark night of the soul. So when you
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.84,1:19:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,decide you're going to be loving towards\Neverybody,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.28,1:19:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,your hatred for your great uncle Louie\Ncomes up.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.08,1:20:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How he screwed you out of a pair of\Ntires and never gave him back.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.23,1:20:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So it doesn't mean you are worse. It\Nmeans that you are going through the
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.00,1:20:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,process of purification.\NI wanted to say a little bit before I
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.40,1:20:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,get carried away with whatever subject I\Nget carried away with. Uh
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.36,1:20:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to discover uh discuss meditation\Nstyles and you know I contrasted
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.84,1:20:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,meditation and contemplation.\NContemplation is a way of being in the
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.32,1:20:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,world and um it serves you all the time.\NMeditation is rather specific. It tends
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.80,1:20:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to become limited in time and place.\NIt often starts out with great
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.44,1:20:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,enthusiasm\Nand then diminishes because the baby's
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.15,1:20:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,diaper needs changing. The phone is\Nringing and uh there goes your mitt and
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.56,1:21:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,there so sitting cross-legged and go and\Ndoing and stuff and and shaving your
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.84,1:21:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,head and all and wearing sandals and\Nshorts, you know, will only carry you so
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.48,1:21:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,far. And then you got to become that in\Nthe world, which is a whole different
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.48,1:21:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,ballgame. So, you know, pick a phrase\Nfor the day and live with it. 91st
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.56,1:21:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Psalm, any any great teaching, uh, and\Nlive with it. You know, I used to
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.67,1:21:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,contemplate one, uh, sentence a month,\Nuh, the 91st Psalm. Um, because you you
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.44,1:21:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you live with that and as you live with\Nthat, it re it becomes self-revealing.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.92,1:21:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not one of discovery, it's one of\Nrevelation.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.40,1:21:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of being yang, you become very\Nyin. So the commitment to spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.96,1:21:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,endeavor is a very yang kind of a\Ncommitment.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.96,1:21:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You know in my own case it was including\Ndeath itself. Whatever it took to get
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.88,1:22:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,there which took me to the depths of\Nhell.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.48,1:22:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But the drive was yang unstoppable.\NNothing physical death. The terrors of
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.28,1:22:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,hell nothing stood back. It was very\Nyang. But then the process as it
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.56,1:22:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,unfolded was very very yin.\NAnd as Dr. Colinbach said to me the
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.19,1:22:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,other day, uh he says it's ultra yin.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.71,1:22:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. So the commitment is ultra yang,\Nbut the process is ultra lin yin. to
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.00,1:22:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,step back and surrender and the along\Nthis now that you've stated what your
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.63,1:22:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,goal is\Nthe process you've triggered the process
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.36,1:22:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,then the process of purification\Nyou surrender everything to God as as it
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.56,1:22:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,arises\Ncondemning yourself for past faults
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.19,1:23:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,wallowing in guilt self-punitive blame\Nis cured by will being willing to
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.84,1:23:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,surrender that judgment to God because\Nat the time you did the best that you
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.36,1:23:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,could do knowing what you knew at the\Ntime being what you were at the time and
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.56,1:23:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of course now you would choose\Ndifferently
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.67,1:23:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but then isn't now and you aren't you\Nweren't then what you are now so it's
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.36,1:23:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,difficult to get by self judgment unless\Nyou're willing to surrender it to God
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.15,1:23:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. So that's how you bypass some of\Nthe difficult things that come up. And
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.44,1:23:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,when we get to the dualities, we'll\Nspeak of them more specifically.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.56,1:23:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes people act about ask about\Nmeditative styles. You know, I was a
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.19,1:23:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,consultant to every kind of a religious\Norganization back east including the Zen
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.19,1:23:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,monastery. I myself was a member of the\Nfirst Zen monastery in New York, first
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.67,1:23:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Zen Institute in New York and did Zen\Nmeditation etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.80,1:24:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm very familiar with all kinds of\Nmeditation meditations.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.88,1:24:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh\Nthere's really three simple styles.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.92,1:24:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There's all kinds of books. There's\Nwhole libraries of meditation. There's
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.80,1:24:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,whole spiritual disciplines that go back\Nfor centuries.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.88,1:24:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh but there they fall into really three\Ncategories. And I believe in
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.00,1:24:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,demystifying them. Demystifying them.\Nthe simplest meditative style.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.04,1:24:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh and I meditated an hour twice a day\Nfor 20 years and then came out west and
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.28,1:24:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,meditated uh like all day every day for\Nsome years.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.08,1:24:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a simple meditative style you\Ncan do anytime anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.08,1:24:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh it if you are able to close your\Neyes, don't do this one while you're
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.92,1:24:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,driving.\NI put this label on the bottom of this.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.67,1:25:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not do while driving.\NClose eyes. And uh if you if you merely
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.63,1:25:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,close your eyes, which I'm doing right\Nnow, uh you'll notice that you don't
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.71,1:25:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,have total darkness. There's little tiny\Nuh specks of light. If you just close
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.44,1:25:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,your eyes, you'll notice there's little\Ntiny specks of light.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.12,1:25:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,uh those are called um spheronmes uh\Nlittle light impulses in the nerves uh
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.23,1:25:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,itself. If you close your eyes and just\Nlook straight ahead, you'll see a black
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.92,1:25:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,dark field and in it are a million\Nlittle speckles of light sort of varying
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.28,1:25:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in different color and\Nuh etc. Is that so? Anybody don't see
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.63,1:25:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that?\NOkay, they're there.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.56,1:25:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Just got to notice that maybe you got a\Nmental thing that when you close your
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.15,1:26:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,eyes, everything turns black. It does\Nnot turn black. It does not turn black.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.23,1:26:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,No, those little spherronomes or spheros\Nsomething or others
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.12,1:26:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,look like little tiny little bitty\Nthings. All right. So if you do nothing
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.67,1:26:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but breathe quietly and uh look at them\Nand do nothing but look at them.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.44,1:26:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Do nothing but look at them.\NAs you look at them
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.04,1:26:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you uh you're not interested in what the\Nmind is saying. It's sort of irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.28,1:26:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You you become eventually emerge with\Nthe little light spec spectacles and you
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.12,1:26:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,transcend thought and thinkingness.\NYou enter a silent
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.88,1:26:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,underneath thinkingness is a profound\Nfield of silence.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.23,1:26:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,99% of the mind is silent. Only 1% is\Ntalking.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.32,1:26:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,As you so you merge with the field, you\Nbecome one with the little speckles
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.71,1:27:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,which are nonverbal, non-intellectual,\Nand you're already out of the
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.88,1:27:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,thinkingness. You're already beyond 400.\NYou're into phenomena. So you become one
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.88,1:27:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,with the phenomena. You're witnessing a\Nphenomena.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.88,1:27:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So even as I'm talking now, you close\Nyour eyes and don't pay attention to the
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.32,1:27:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,speaker.\NYou just look at the little tiny specks
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.36,1:27:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and do nothing but become\Nmerge with the specs.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.52,1:27:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,As you do that, eventually the total\Ncontext
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.08,1:27:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,uh how should we say the whole context\Nof your beingness will begin to expand
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.60,1:27:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,will begin to expand. There's no longer\Na me looking at a them.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.44,1:27:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The lookingness, the experiencing\Nis a total oneness.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.60,1:28:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You can very quickly bypass duality,\Nthinkingness, and thinking mind. Very
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.23,1:28:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,simple. You can do it on the bus, on the\Nsubway.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.08,1:28:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it in the doctor's waiting\Nroom. You can do it any place.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.48,1:28:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it just when you got nothing\Nelse to do. Uh it's the simplest med and
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.52,1:28:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the fastest meditation style I know. If\Nyou're going to be conscious of anything
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.00,1:28:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,else other than the little specules of\Nlight inside your eyelids, the only
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.48,1:28:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,other thing would be the be be one with\Nthe breathing. So you can be one with
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.36,1:28:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the breathing and then the spicules of\Nlight and then forget the breathing and
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.40,1:28:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you become one with the light. uh\Ninstantly not instantly but relatively
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.80,1:28:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,rapidly your whole state of\Nconsciousness will expand and you may go
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.80,1:28:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,through certain phases which you come to\Nrecognize every time you do it I used to
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.56,1:28:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,call uh shortly after you start it you\Nhit a thing in which the whole field
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.96,1:28:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,turns an intense blue I would say that's\Nthe stage of the blue then beyond the
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.08,1:29:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,blue is another and you will it will be\Nas though you're going through various
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.80,1:29:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,dimensions\Nmore and more expanded dimensions
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.23,1:29:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of the\Nof of the field of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.08,1:29:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,See, because you're starting from the\Nwitness observer and then you go past
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.08,1:29:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the phenomenology of the witness\Nobserver uh to the infinite field of
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.88,1:29:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness itself which is totally\Nnonlinear and has no confines.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.84,1:29:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very rapid way to go beyond\Nanything.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.52,1:29:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't take\Nuh much to do it. You can do it anytime,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.52,1:29:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,any place. And you go into sort of a\Nbliss state.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.23,1:29:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh people get annoyed that you're\Nalways closing your eyes when you're
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.36,1:29:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,talking to me. Stop closing your eyes\Nwhen you talk to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.71,1:29:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because you go into a bliss state.\NSo you find yourself blissing out in
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.19,1:30:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,this state all the time. You know, it's\Nvery fast and easy.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.56,1:30:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's the way through the mind.\NThe way through the mind
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.67,1:30:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is more classic meditation\Nis uh witnessing the phenomena of the
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.67,1:30:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,mind. You see thoughts arising and\Nfalling away. And we've talked about
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.40,1:30:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that in prior lectures\Nthat the thinkingness what you think is
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.44,1:30:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking isn't thinking anyway. It's\Nmentalizing.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.76,1:30:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Mentalizing is not thinking. People say\NI was thinking all day. They weren't
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.44,1:30:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking about anything. I say to you,\N"Well, what brilliant new think did you
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.60,1:30:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,come up with?" They haven't got any.\NThey were foraging through the past,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.76,1:30:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,anticipating the future, images of all\Nkinds of things. They M&M's off
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.40,1:30:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,television, wagging dogs tails,\Nhorrible pictures they just got on the
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.60,1:30:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,day news. It's\Nnot thinking, that's imaging. So this
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.96,1:31:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,computer\NTV screen. So what you then then do in
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.00,1:31:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,classic meditation sit down cross-legged\Ndo the whole deal and um stop eating
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.63,1:31:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,meat too. See and become a vegetarian\Nand live on brown rice. That helps the
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.67,1:31:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,whole deal.\NTake off clothes. Live on brown rice.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.67,1:31:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Sit cross-legged. Get your head shaved.\NAll right. So then you you're witnessing
Dialogue: 0,1:31:30.40,1:31:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the phenomena of the mind. You're not\Nwitnessing thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.80,1:31:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And the purpose of it is to withdraw\Ninto the witness observer. You become
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.32,1:31:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the witness of the phenomena instead of\Nthe subject. And as you do that, as you
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.48,1:31:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,move into witness observer,\Nyou it suddenly dawns on you there is no
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.84,1:31:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,me doing the thinking. Not am I not only\Nam I not the mind and the thinking there
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.71,1:32:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,really isn't any thinking going on\Nthere's mentalization and I am not even
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.96,1:32:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the mentalization the sense of is\Nwithdrawn
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.28,1:32:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,from the content of the mind as it plays\Nacross the television screen
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.92,1:32:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the way through the mind there's\Na third way which I can't Remember
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.80,1:32:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,what did I say? Don't forget to mention\Nuh
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.76,1:32:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,three meditative styles. I don't\Nremember what they were now, but they
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.08,1:32:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,must have. You can't become enlightened\Nwithout them.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.88,1:33:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The mantra\N>> yeah contemplation uh a mantra you know
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.44,1:33:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,has\Nwe calibrate them they can be quite high
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.12,1:33:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the difficulty with the mantra is that\Nyou sometimes you're only with it when
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.48,1:33:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you're doing the mantra and the downside\Nof mantra is self-hypnosis you go into
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.12,1:33:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,an autohypnotic you go into an altered\Nstate of consciousness rather than an
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.84,1:33:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced state of consciousness.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.76,1:33:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can any kind of repetitive\Nmovement and spiritual religion
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.63,1:33:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,historically is full of it. Ringing of\Nbells, cranking of prayer wheels,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.52,1:33:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,anything that's repetitious and\Nrepetitious and repetitious and
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.96,1:33:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,repetitious and repetitious\Nmay take you into an altered state of
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.08,1:33:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness. It's an altered state of\Nconsciousness is not a spiritual state.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.88,1:33:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You can go into an alpha state with a\Nyou know alpha wave training and various
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.23,1:34:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,techniques. Um\Nthe consequence of the mantra then is
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.40,1:34:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,based on your intention of what you\Nexpect it to do for you etc. Also the
